                  </hi>, Sen, I was with my son, the last witness. I saw the prisoner pick the prosecutor's pocket—i do not know what became of the handkerchief—I went after the prosecutor, and asked if he had lost any thing—he said his handkerchief—I asked him to step back with me, which he did—the officer had the prisoner and the other in hand—the other got away.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner's Defence</hi>. I had been to Greenwich fair, and got intoxicated. I was about to leave a friend, when the officer came and charged me with picking a gentleman's pocket.</p>
